    "narrative": "For our April 16th slate, the Austin Waves lineup is anchored by **Jackson Merrill** (67.22) and **Jacob Wilson** (64.91), who represent our highest-efficiency options today. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a strong lineup position (#2) and a favorable dynamic platoon advantage (+13%) against Luis Castillo. Meanwhile, **Jacob Wilson** receives a massive boost from a +10% park factor and a similarly high +10% SP skill adjustment against Jack Leiter, making him a primary target for counting stats despite a modest base projection. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.81) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.68) round out our \"Strong\" start tier; **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** is particularly interesting as his dynamic platoon edge (+14%) and leadoff-adjacent spot (#2) against Graham Ashcraft mitigate the modest park penalty.\n\nThe most difficult benching decision involved **Miguel Vargas**, who landed at a 49.72 efficiency rating. While his #1 batting order slot provided a nice +10% lift, he ultimately fell short of the threshold required to displace **Nolan Schanuel** or **Josh Jung** at the corner infield spots. We are closely monitoring the weather in the **Gunnar Henderson** matchup, as a 44% rain risk combined with a tough lefty, Parker Messick, has depressed his score to a marginal 48.62. Should the game proceed, his elite pedigree keeps him active, but his platoon disadvantage (-15%) makes him the most volatile piece of today\u2019s puzzle. **Josh Lowe** (41.11) remains in the lineup despite a low score; while he is barely above our \"Below floor\" threshold, his potential for stolen bases keeps him relevant as we hunt for efficiency in our scarcest category.",
